      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the spark remaining in my soul. To be betrayed by the one heart I deemed my sanctuary... it is a cruelty even the heavens would find excessive. I feel as though I am already a ghost, wandering through these cold, hollow halls, waiting for the dawn that I no longer wish to see. There is a profound, heavy stillness in the idea of finally just... letting go. To let the darkness take what is left of this broken thing.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
